  "texts": [
    "CNNs (LeCun, 1989) were originally applied to image recognition.",
    "The convolution and pooling layers in CNNs can extract the distinguishing features of the given data while reducing the number of data to be processed (Ajit et al., 2020).",
    "Consequently, CNNs are highly effective in processing data that come in the form of multiple arrays.",
    "For time series' data, 1D-CNNs can extract local temporal features via convolution kernels that slide along the time dimension.",
    "The 1D-CNNs have demonstrated success in speech and natural language processing applications (Abdel-Hamid et al., 2014; Severyn and Moschitti, 2015)."
  ],
